# Workplace Safety Web App — Implementation Plan

A pre-sale demo web application for the **Workplace Safety / PPE Detection** use case, following the same architecture as the existing Lead Scoring project. The app demonstrates how Dataiku-powered AI models can detect PPE compliance (helmets, vests, masks) from images/video, display real-time alerts, and provide comprehensive safety analytics.

**Target directory**: `c:\work\pre_sale\DS_service\object_detect\factory_safety`

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph LR
  A[Next.js Frontend<br/>Port 3000] -->|REST API| B[FastAPI Backend<br/>Port 8080]
  B -->|dataikuapi / REST| C[Dataiku DSS<br/>Model Inference]
  B -->|Read/Write| D[(SQLite / JSON<br/>Local Storage)]
```

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Frontend | Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, ShadCN UI, Recharts, Framer Motion | UI & visualization |
| Backend | FastAPI, Python, Pydantic | API gateway, file handling, report generation |
| AI/ML | Dataiku DSS API | Object detection model inference |
| Storage | SQLite (or JSON files for demo) | Incident logs, detection history |

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Dataiku API Endpoint**: The plan assumes the Dataiku object detection model is accessible via `dataikuapi` or a REST scoring endpoint. Please confirm:
> 1. The Dataiku project key (e.g., `OBJECT_DETECTION`)
> 2. The scoring endpoint ID or API service name
> 3. Whether the model accepts base64-encoded images or multipart file uploads

> [!NOTE]
> **Demo Mode**: All pages will ship with realistic mock data so the app works standalone without a Dataiku connection. The backend will gracefully fall back to mock responses when Dataiku is unreachable.

